<item>
            <title>[WFMP-29] Using the start goal leaves a rouge reaper which could shutdown containers started after</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFMP-29</link>
                <project id="12316025" key="WFMP">WildFly Maven Plugin</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;start&lt;/tt&gt; goal has a reaper thread that checks whether the server is still running and if not it attempts to shut it down. The problem is this keeps running even after the &lt;tt&gt;stop&lt;/tt&gt; goal has been executed. Any process started after this, for example an Arquillian container, the reaper thread may shutdown the container.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
